00:31:42.440 --> 00:31:45.417
So this is a
definition that I got,

00:31:45.417 --> 00:31:47.000
I think from one of
the [? reasons, ?]

00:31:47.000 --> 00:31:50.240
so technological
processes and resources

00:31:50.240 --> 00:31:52.910
that are used, created,
or managed for learning

00:31:52.910 --> 00:31:56.030
and/or improving performance.

00:31:56.030 --> 00:31:58.910
So that's crazy broad.

00:31:58.910 --> 00:32:02.600
And then in that definition,
there's this technological,

00:32:02.600 --> 00:32:05.090
which gets around
the electronic,

00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:06.520
but brings back
the idea of well,

00:32:06.520 --> 00:32:09.260
a blackboard is probably a
technology at some level,

00:32:09.260 --> 00:32:11.240
or at least it
was at some point.

00:32:11.240 --> 00:32:21.890
So it's admittedly an incredibly
difficult concept to pin down.

00:32:21.890 --> 00:32:24.335
And maybe at some point, you
don't necessarily have to.

00:32:24.335 --> 00:32:28.030
You have to decide which slice
of it you want to deal with.

00:32:28.030 --> 00:32:32.791
And so the other important
thing is that it's--

00:32:32.791 --> 00:32:35.290
and it doesn't have to be, but
it can be-- an integral part.

00:32:35.290 --> 00:32:41.690
Or it should be well-integrated
within the course,

00:32:41.690 --> 00:32:46.330
and or it could be a
supplemental learning aid.

00:32:46.330 --> 00:32:47.890
So it could be a
way of delivering

00:32:47.890 --> 00:32:53.620
content outside of class,
or the idea of an enrichment

00:32:53.620 --> 00:32:54.940
of the material.

00:32:54.940 --> 00:32:57.190
And it could be
something like hardware,

00:32:57.190 --> 00:32:59.618
really just like hardware.

00:33:02.300 --> 00:33:07.300
I'm going to come back to how we
chop this up in just a second.

00:33:07.300 --> 00:33:09.642
Remember that we
don't want to do

00:33:09.642 --> 00:33:12.100
any thing-- this is the idea
about walking into Home Depot.

00:33:12.100 --> 00:33:14.350
We don't want to do anything
without thinking first

00:33:14.350 --> 00:33:16.360
about our intended
learning outcomes.

00:33:16.360 --> 00:33:18.880
What intended learning outcome
is the technology going

00:33:18.880 --> 00:33:24.460
to advance, not, what am I going
to do with this technology?

00:33:24.460 --> 00:33:28.350
And so in terms
of categorization,

00:33:28.350 --> 00:33:30.570
this is something that
I came up with just

00:33:30.570 --> 00:33:31.980
after grappling with things.

00:33:31.980 --> 00:33:33.779
So this is just my thing.

00:33:33.779 --> 00:33:35.820
And we're going to talk
more about different ways

00:33:35.820 --> 00:33:36.640
to think about it.

00:33:36.640 --> 00:33:38.124
So this is just one slice of it.

00:33:38.124 --> 00:33:39.540
You could think
about technologies

00:33:39.540 --> 00:33:41.520
that you use in the
classroom, so that

00:33:41.520 --> 00:33:45.810
would be clickers, that would
be using some sort of projection

00:33:45.810 --> 00:33:49.440
system, using a smart board,
using some sort of simulations

00:33:49.440 --> 00:33:54.030
that you show students, et
cetera, like virtual demos.

00:33:54.030 --> 00:33:58.320
It could be a way for students
to engage with the content

00:33:58.320 --> 00:34:01.470
and with other students
outside of the classroom.

00:34:01.470 --> 00:34:05.130
So it could be some sort of a
wiki, some other collaboration

00:34:05.130 --> 00:34:08.639
tool, and/or it
could be something

00:34:08.639 --> 00:34:11.470
that delivers the content to
the student outside of class.

00:34:15.239 --> 00:34:16.429
And there may be an overlap.

00:34:16.429 --> 00:34:17.989
You may show a
simulation in class,

00:34:17.989 --> 00:34:20.449
and then decide students
should have access to it

00:34:20.449 --> 00:34:21.730
outside of class.

00:34:21.730 --> 00:34:25.550
So they're not
mutually exclusive.

00:34:25.550 --> 00:34:27.260
And so the engagement
with the content

00:34:27.260 --> 00:34:31.940
can include these collaboration
tools, extra materials,

00:34:31.940 --> 00:34:34.010
content enrichment materials.

00:34:34.010 --> 00:34:37.969
And then the third one might
be student assignments.

00:34:37.969 --> 00:34:42.290
So the idea, maybe you're
going to say to students,

00:34:42.290 --> 00:34:45.260
